#!/bin/bash
# custom-workflow-hooks.sh.template - Template for customizing MAF autonomous workflow
#
# ABOUT THIS TEMPLATE:
#   This file provides 8 extension hooks for customizing the MAF autonomous workflow
#   behavior. Franchisees can copy this template and implement custom logic without
#   modifying MAF HQ files.
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Copy this template to your project root:
#      cp maf/templates/custom-workflow-hooks.sh.template custom-workflow-hooks.sh
#   2. Implement the hooks you need (see examples below)
#   3. Make the file executable: chmod +x custom-workflow-hooks.sh
#   4. Run your workflow script with the hooks file:
#      export MAF_CUSTOM_HOOKS="$(pwd)/custom-workflow-hooks.sh"
#      bash experiments/autonomous-workflow-nextnest.sh
#
# INTEGRATION:
#   The autonomous workflow script will:
#   - Check for MAF_CUSTOM_HOOKS environment variable
#   - Source the hooks file if specified
#   - Call each hook function at the appropriate point in the workflow
#   - Gracefully handle missing hooks (use default behavior)
#
# DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
#   - Non-breaking: Missing hooks or hook files don't stop the workflow
#   - Explicit: Hooks are called at well-defined points in the execution
#   - Flexible: Each hook can return different status codes to control flow
#   - Safe: Errors in hooks are caught and logged without crashing the workflow
#
# HOOK REFERENCE:
#   1. HOOK_BEFORE_LOOP    - Initialization before main loop starts
#   2. HOOK_BEFORE_CHECK   - Before checking agent status each iteration
#   3. HOOK_BEFORE_ASSIGN  - Before assigning a bead to an agent
#   4. HOOK_AFTER_ASSIGN   - After successful bead assignment
#   5. HOOK_CUSTOM_BEAD    - Custom bead type handler (bypasses default assignment)
#   6. HOOK_AGENT_PROMPT   - Modify commands sent to agents
#   7. HOOK_AFTER_CHECK    - After checking agent status each iteration
#   8. HOOK_ERROR_HANDLER  - Global error recovery handler
#
# EXIT CODES:
#   Each hook can return:
#   0 - Continue with default behavior
#   1 - Skip current operation (context-dependent)
#   2 - Abort/exit workflow (use sparingly)
#
# BEST PRACTICES:
#   - Keep hooks fast (avoid long-running operations)
#   - Use advisory warnings for non-critical issues
#   - Log all custom actions with clear timestamps
#   - Test hooks in isolation before production use
#   - Document what each hook does and why it's needed
#   - Return quickly (avoid blocking the main loop)
#
# SEE ALSO:
#   - docs/VENDOR_ARCHITECTURE.md - Proper customization channels
#   - maf/templates/custom-preflight-checks.sh.template - Preflight customizations
#   - tests/workflow/fixtures/custom-hooks-example.sh - Minimal working examples

